    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-24T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-24T12:00:00-05:00" n="819"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/10–2446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-24T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 24, 1946—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1918. From Connolly and Vogelback for Donald Davis FLC. Please radio present
                    situation re Kiang matter. If satisfactory progress not being made, this office
                    supports you in approach to General Marshall. If further action on Washington
                    level is desired please advise. All possible expedition is desired to avoid
                    assumption that delay implies consent.</p>
                <p>Sent to Shanghai as 1918, repeated to Manila as 541. [Connolly and
                    Vogelback.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
